<div class="top" style="height:auto;">
    <h3 >Ingredients:</h3>
    <ul>

        <li> 60 grams butter</li>
        <li>45 ml  Vegetable oil</li>
        <li>1 cup powdered Sugar</li>
        <li>1/2 cup Condensed Milk</li>
        <li>1 tbsp Vanilla extract</li>
        <li>1+1/2 cup All Purpose Flour</li>
        <li>1/4th cup Cornflour</li>
        <li>1 cup Cocoa poeder</li>
        <li>1+1/4th  tsp Baking Powder</li>
        <li>1 tsp Baking Soda</li>
        <li>1 cup Boiling hot water</li>
        <li>1/2 cup Milk at room temperature</li>
        <li>1/2 tbsp Vinegar</li>
        <li>simple sugar syrup at room temperature(equal parts of water and sugar boiled for 2-3 mins )</li>
        
    </ul>
    <h3>
        For Ganache:
    </h3>
    <uL>
        <li>400 ml fresh cream(I prefer Amul)</li>
        <li>350 grams 70% Dark chocolate</li>
        <li>1 tbsp Vanilla extract</li>
    </uL>

   
</div>
<div class="top" style="height:auto;">
    <h3>Method:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Preheat the oven at 180C for 10-15 mins.</li>
        <li>Add Vinegar to 1/2 cup of milk at room temperature and keep aside.</li>
        <li>Add Butter,oil & powdered sugar to a big bowl and whisk well until pale and creamy.</li>
        <li>Add condensed milk and vanilla extract and  whisk well for another 3-4 mins.</li>
        <li>Sift flour, cornflour, baking powder and baking soda in a separate bowl.</li>
        <li>Add half of flour mix to the butter mix and add half of milk-vinegar mixture and mix gently.</li>
        <li>Add remaining flour and adjust the consistency(ribbon like consistency) with remaining milk-vinegar mixture and mix well.</li>
        <li style="color:red">Donot overmix the batter</li>
        <li>Boil 1 cup of water and remove from heat. Add 1 cup of cocoa powder and mix well.</li>
        <li> Add bloomed cocoa mix to the cake batter and mix gently with a spatula.</li>
        <li>Pour in 2 6" cake tins(greased and lined) and bake in a preheated oven for 20-25 minutes or until a skewer comes out clean.</li>
        <li>For ganache:</li>
        <li>Chop the chocolate into small peices and add to a bog bowl.</li>
        <li>Heat the cream till it is hot and pour over the chocolate peices and keep aside for 10 mins.</li>

        <li>Gently stir the mixture till well combined, cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.</li>
        <li> Whip the ganache for 3-4 mins or till it is light brown in color.</li>
        
        
    </ul>
</div>
